cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category as it focuses on Anomaly-based Network Intrusion Detection System (A-NIDS) for detecting network attacks. The use of Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) architecture for processing time series and Support Vector Data Description (SVDD) for anomaly detection suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The joint optimization method used in the proposed model could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the focus on analyzing network traffic and observing trends of behaviors over a period of time could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
